Description: Rim sherd of Corinthian, probably black-figured, pottery column-krater; interior and exterior of rim glazed black; rays on top; inscription on top.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Curator's comments: For parallels, see Dunbabin (ed.), ‘Perachora - Vol. II: Pottery, Ivories, Scarabs and other Objects. The Sanctuaries of Hera Akraia and Limenia’, Clarendon Press, Oxford (1962), pl. 69, fig. 2245.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.163) (phase 3)
